    <span property="dc:title" content="Poor Conditions at Pennsylvania Jail Heighten COVID-19 Concerns" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>

  <header class="article-header">
    <footer class="article-header__footer">
      <div class="dateline"><time class="date" datetime="2020-04-08T15:37:22-04:00">April 8, 2020 3:37PM EDT</time> <span class="type">Dispatches</span></div>
            </footer>
          <h1 id="page-title" class="title--huge">Poor Conditions at Pennsylvania Jail Heighten COVID-19 Concerns</h1>
              <p class="subtitle">Authorities Should Move Swiftly on Releases</p>
    
    
          <address class="article-author clearfix">
        
  <div class="field field--field-shared-author">
    <article class="node node-profile has-image byline--expanded clearfix"  about="/about/people/allison-frankel" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">
      <figure class="byline-image">
      <a href="/about/people/allison-frankel">
        <img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/square_small/public/multimedia_images_2019/201910us_allison_frankel.jpg?itok=NshUXS1f" width="108" height="108" alt="Allison Frankel" />      </a>
    </figure>
        <h4 class="name">
              <a href="/about/people/allison-frankel">
              Allison Frankel              </a>
          </h4>
  <span property="dc:title" content="Allison Frankel" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>      <span class="position">2019 - 2021 Aryeh Neier Fellow, US Program</span>
    </article>
  </div>
      </address>
      </header>
  <div class="article-utilities article-utilities--fixed clearfix">
          <div class="article-share">
        <button class="article-share-toggle toggle">Share</button>
        <p class="minimal-share"><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Poor%20Conditions%20at%20Pennsylvania%20Jail%20Heighten%20COVID-19%20Concerns%20https%3A//www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns" class="twitter icon" data-width="600" data-height="260"></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A//www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns" class="facebook icon" data-width="600" data-height="500"></a><a href="whatsapp://send?text=Poor%20Conditions%20at%20Pennsylvania%20Jail%20Heighten%20COVID-19%20Concerns%20-%20https%3A//www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns" class="whatsapp icon ms-mobile-only" data-width="455" data-height="455"></a><a href="mailto:?subject=Poor%20Conditions%20at%20Pennsylvania%20Jail%20Heighten%20COVID-19%20Concerns&amp;body=https%3A//www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns" class="email icon"></a><a href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&amp;url=https%3A//www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns&amp;title=Poor%20Conditions%20at%20Pennsylvania%20Jail%20Heighten%20COVID-19%20Concerns" class="linkedin icon" data-width="520" data-height="570"></a><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=https%3A//www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns" class="gplus icon" data-width="600" data-height="400"></a><a href="http://reddit.com/submit?url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns&amp;title=Poor Conditions at Pennsylvania Jail Heighten COVID-19 Concerns" class="reddit icon" data-width="600" data-height="500"></a><a href="https://telegram.me/share/url?url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/04/08/poor-conditions-pennsylvania-jail-heighten-covid-19-concerns&amp;text=Poor Conditions at Pennsylvania Jail Heighten COVID-19 Concerns" class="telegram icon" data-width="600" data-height="500"></a></p>
      </div>
        <div class="article-print">
       <a href="/print/340592"><button class="button--print">Print</button></a>
    </div>
  </div>



  
  
  <div class="article-content article-content--sidebar clearfix" >
    <div class="article-content__primary l-primary">
      <div class="article-body article-body--contained">
        
        <p>Twelve people at George W. Hill Correctional Facility (GHCF) in Delaware County, Pennsylvania recently <a href="https://kywnewsradio.radio.com/articles/news/coronavirus-in-delco-jail-spurs-expedited-release-of-inmates">tested positive</a> for COVID-19, raising serious concerns. Jails and prisons are <a href="https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/03/12/us-covid-19-threatens-people-behind-bars">incubators</a> of <a href="https://www.npr.org/2020/03/13/815002735/prisons-and-jails-worry-about-becoming-coronavirus-incubators">infectious diseases</a> like COVID-19, but conditions at GHCF make it particularly <a href="https://theappeal.org/jails-coronavirus-covid-19-pandemic-flattening-curve/">vulnerable to outbreaks</a>, putting people inside <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/30/opinion/nyc-prison-release-covid.html">and outside</a> the facility at risk.</p>
<div class="embed" data-type="image">
<figure class="embed node node-image align-right multimedia"  about="/video-photos/photograph/2020/04/08/202004us-jail-ghcf" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">
    <span property="dc:title" content="202004us_jail_ghcf" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  <div class="embed-media">
          <a href="/view-mode/modal/340591" class="link--modal link--inline-block">
        <img  alt="The George W. Hill Correctional Facility (GHCF) in Delaware County, Pennsylvania" sizes="(min-width: 77.5em) 946px, (min-width: 48em) calc(100vw - 120px), (min-width: 37.5em) calc(100vw - 70px), calc(100vw - 50px)" data-srcset="https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/294w/public/multimedia_images_2020/202004us_jail_ghcf.jpg?itok=-_Fzx0BM 294w, https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/430w/public/multimedia_images_2020/202004us_jail_ghcf.jpg?itok=iVNeY3KB 430w, https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/676w/public/multimedia_images_2020/202004us_jail_ghcf.jpg?itok=f-UcC1hx 676w, https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/946w/public/multimedia_images_2020/202004us_jail_ghcf.jpg?itok=PF5WVsQy 946w, https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/1070w/public/multimedia_images_2020/202004us_jail_ghcf.jpg?itok=kQut5a-q 1070w" data-src="https://www.hrw.org/sites/default/files/styles/16x9_946x534/public/multimedia_images_2020/202004us_jail_ghcf.jpg?itok=6xykmZd1" class="js-unveil" />      </a>
              <div class="embed-actions embed-actions--expand">
        <a href="/view-mode/modal/340591" class="link--modal">Expand</a>
      </div>
      </div>

      <figcaption class="figure-info clearfix">
              <span class="figure-caption"><p>The George W. Hill Correctional Facility (GHCF) in Delaware County, Pennsylvania.</p>
</span>
                    <span class="figure-credit">© Human Rights Watch</span>
          </figcaption>
  
</figure>
</div>
<p>Human Rights Watch visited the jail in October 2019 as part of research into <a href="https://www.inquirer.com/news/inq/probation-parole-pennsylvania-philadelphia-criminal-justice-system-20191024.html">high incarceration rates</a> across the <a href="https://www.bjs.gov/content/pub/pdf/ppus16.pdf">United States</a> for <a href="https://www.pewtrusts.org/en/research-and-analysis/issue-briefs/2018/09/probation-and-parole-systems-marked-by-high-stakes-missed-opportunities">probation and parole violations</a>, often for minor conduct like <a href="https://justicelab.columbia.edu/sites/default/files/content/PACommunityCorrections4.19.18finalv3.pdf">missing required meetings</a>, <a href="https://csgjusticecenter.org/publications/confined-costly/">using drugs</a>, and moving residences without permission.</p>
<p>We spoke with individuals held in GHCF and a guard, who described rampant overcrowding and unsanitary conditions.</p>
<p>Officials at the jail regularly hold many people together in one intake cell for several days, sometimes more. On the day we spoke to a guard, 59 people were housed in the cell, which has no beds or toilets, the guard said. Guards sometimes deny requests to use a bathroom, leaving people to urinate on themselves or into milk cartons.</p>
<p>Some formerly incarcerated at GHCF report <a href="https://delcocpr.org/our-stories">similar conditions</a> and have filed <a href="https://cases.justia.com/federal/district-courts/pennsylvania/paedce/2:2018cv04852/549401/6/0.pdf?ts=1545302874">lawsuits</a> <a href="https://www.casemine.com/judgement/us/5af94e293f5bae2082278827">making</a> <a href="https://casetext.com/case/allen-v-george-w-hill-corr-prison">similar</a> <a href="https://www.docketbird.com/court-documents/Richardson-v-George-W-Hill-Correctional-Facility/MEMORANDUM-AND-OR-OPINION-OF-3-12-2019-SIGNED-BY-JUDGE-EDWARD-G-SMITH-ON-3-12-2019-3-12-2019-ENTERED-AND-COPIES-MAILED-AND-E-MAILED/paed-2:2019-cv-00536-00006">claims</a>, prompting the formation of an <a href="https://delcocpr.org/">advocacy organization</a> aimed at reforming the jail.</p>
<p>Since the coronavirus pandemic, officials have <a href="https://www.delcotimes.com/news/coronavirus/delco-courts-d-a-move-to-reduce-prison-population/article_6a9a5c36-6fb2-11ea-9238-335cefed70bc.html">reduced GHCF’s population</a> from 1,880 to <a href="https://www.delcopa.gov/publicrelations/releases/2020/gwhprotection.html">1,387</a>. Authorities have also <a href="https://www.altoonamirror.com/news/local-news/2020/04/prisons-cope-with-covid-19/">released people</a> from other facilities and are reviewing more.</p>
<p>A reporter said that Darrell Bassett, who was detained at GHCF on misdemeanor marijuana charges, was <a href="https://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2020/04/01/coronavirus-pennsylvania-quarantined-george-hill-correctional-facility-inmate-darrell-bassett-with-103-degree-fever-claims-prison-doing-nothing-for-us-here/">sick with</a> COVID-19 and on a county list of individuals <a href="https://6abc.com/area-officials-work-to-thin-jail-prison-populations-amid-covid-19/6057143/">eligible for release</a>. But officials would not release him due to a parole “detainer” from another county.</p>
<p>Many of the <a href="https://www.prisonpolicy.org/profiles/PA.html">37,000 people confined</a> in Pennsylvania’s jails are, like Bassett, in on <a href="https://www.prisonpolicy.org/blog/2020/03/18/detainers/#fnref:2">detainers</a>. These require people to <a href="https://www.inquirer.com/news/inq/probation-parole-pennsylvania-philadelphia-detainer-criminal-justice-system-20191227.html">stay in jail</a>, sometimes for weeks or months, waiting for hearings to determine whether they violated their probation or parole conditions. Following a recent <a href="https://www.aclupa.org/en/press-releases/aclu-pennsylvania-asks-state-supreme-court-reduce-county-jail-populations-avert-even">lawsuit</a> challenging jailing during the pandemic, the <a href="https://aclupa.org/en/press-releases/aclu-pa-statement-pennsylvania-supreme-court-rejection-emergency-request-reduce?fbclid=IwAR32fBfd0E1I_2LAqQui2nQF4UdAlPP6lOM2fcJzpkQ_0IG3IQZSecFyAe8">Pennsylvania Supreme Court</a> – while declining to order individuals released – directed courts to find ways to reduce jail populations.</p>
<p>The Pennsylvania Department of Corrections <a href="https://www.wgal.com/article/pa-doc-will-release-information-relating-to-covid-19/31967130">announced</a> on March 28 it will review individual detainers – but real urgency is needed.  </p>
<p>Officials should <a href="https://www.exitprobationparole.org/covid19statement">prioritize</a> <a href="https://www.delcotimes.com/news/coronavirus/advocates-call-for-release-of-inmates-at-county-prison/article_b503bf36-6ded-11ea-b3de-cbf145d48f06.html">for release</a> people not accused of serious offenses who pose no known danger to others, including those held in on detainers, as well as those at <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/need-extra-precautions/people-at-higher-risk.html">high risk</a> of serious effects from the virus, among others.</p>
<p>Swift action to reduce incarceration could mean the difference between life and death for those inside and outside GHCF and similar facilities.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="donation-promo--two-column">
